### PHP Function Parameters

Parameters allow functions to accept input values when called.

### Syntax

```php
<?php
function functionName($param1, $param2) {
    // use parameters
}
?>
```

### Parameter Types

```php
<?php
// Required parameters
function greet($name) {
    echo "Hello, $name";
}

// Default parameters
function greetWithTitle($name, $title = "Mr.") {
    echo "Hello, $title $name";
}

// Type declarations (PHP 7+)
function add(int $a, int $b): int {
    return $a + $b;
}

// Nullable types
function setAge(?int $age) {
    echo "Age: " . ($age ?? "not set");
}

// Variadic parameters (PHP 5.6+)
function sum(...$numbers) {
    return array_sum($numbers);
}

echo sum(1, 2, 3, 4); // 10
?>
```

### Pass by Reference

```php
<?php
function addExclamation(&$str) {
    $str .= "!";
}

$text = "Hello";
addExclamation($text);
echo $text; // Hello!
?>
```

> **Key Point:** By default, parameters are passed by value. Use `&` to pass by reference so the function can modify the original variable.
